title: Update stop_times.txt in sample-feed-1 to be RFC 4180-compliant
body:
According to [RFC 4180](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc4180#section-2), the spec used in the GTFS format, every single record in a CSV file must contain the same amount of fields.

The following file has records of length 9 but from line 17 onward, only 5 fields are defined:
https://github.com/google/transit/blob/daa60b4c500534b1a193a499793da3624c3eeb82/gtfs/spec/en/examples/sample-feed-1/stop_times.txt#L1-L29

This (rudimentary) example feed is part of my test suite for my library which makes some of them fail because of this odd formatting. Since it is unusual behavior and is directly against reference documents, I prefer not to fit this capability in my software as it could accept partial GTFS feeds as valid and provide erroneous data in consequence.

title: [GTFS Fares v2] Semantics clarification
body:
Based on recent discussions in the gtfs-fares Slack channel and working group, clarify some fares v2 related semantics including:

- Introduce a `Local Time` data type to eliminate potential confusion caused by the existing `Time` data type in timeframes.txt.
- Add "effective fare leg" to the general description of fare_transfer_rules.txt
- Add "timer should start from the first matched leg" clarification

Tagging active working group members for review🙏
@felixguendling @westontrillium @jfabi @skinkie @halbertram @evansiroky @miklcct @jll01 @bdferris-v2
